Four packages are delivered to four houses, one to each house. If these packages are randomly delivered, what is the probability that exactly two of them are delivered to the correct houses? Express your answer as a common fraction.
  A. \frac{1}{4}
  B. \frac{27}{128}
  C. \frac{1}{2}
  D. \frac{1}{9}
Answer with just the letter.

3 cards are chosen at random from a standard 52-card deck. What is the probability that they form a pair? (A 3-card hand is a 'pair' if two of the cards match in rank but the third card is different. For example, 668 is a pair, but 999 is not.)
  A. \frac{1}{8}
  B. \frac{1}{36}
  C. \frac{1}{78}
  D. \frac{72}{425}
Answer with just the letter.
